.TH tmpfile 3s 
.SH NAME
tmpfile \- create a temporary file
.SH SYNTAX
.B #include <stdio.h>
.PP
.B
.SM FILE
.B "\(**tmpfile (\|)"
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.PN tmpfile
subroutine creates a temporary file and returns a corresponding
.SM FILE
pointer.
The file will
automatically be deleted when the process using
it terminates.
The file is opened for update.
.SH SEE ALSO
creat(2), unlink(2), fopen(3s), mktemp(3), tmpnam(3s)
